</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="302" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[810,1449,1566,1845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,937,1566,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">Remarks. –</emphasis>
The only species of the genus with hook-like projections on the metafemora known so far was 
<taxonomicName authority="Franz, 1985" authorityName="Franz" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Horaeomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heissi">
<emphasis box="[1353,1449,1599,1622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">H. heissi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Franz H" box="[810,947,1630,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="302" pagination="91 - 128" refId="ref4538" refString="Franz H., 1985. Neue und ungenugend bekannte Scydmaeniden (Coleoptera) aus Taiwan, Fukien und Thailand. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologische Gesellschaft, 74: 91 - 128." type="journal article" year="1985">Franz, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from W 
<collectingCountry box="[1061,1164,1630,1653]" name="Malaysia" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1183,1269,1630,1653]" country="Malaysia" name="Pahang" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">Pahang</collectingRegion>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1339,1448,1630,1653]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[818,914,1662,1685]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
). The latter species is distinctly different in the general body form, it is smaller, more slender and distinctly flatter than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ski" authorityYear="2009" box="[939,1113,1727,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Horaeomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="samosirensis">
<emphasis box="[939,1113,1727,1750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">H. samosirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it also has only slightly bent metafemora, whereas those in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ski" authorityYear="2009" box="[1141,1313,1759,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Horaeomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="samosirensis">
<emphasis box="[1141,1313,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">H. samosirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are strongly bent. This new species is the first 
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1352,1791,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Horaeomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1177,1352,1791,1814]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="302">Horaeomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported to occur in an island located on a lake.
</paragraph>
